      {
        "id": "1uotwJO7vc1RiVeu",
        "title": "Text 5",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<h2>Adding Outputs</h2><p>Did you notice the blocks come in three different colors?</p><ul><li>The purple blocks are called “inputs.” They bring numbers into the program.</li><li>The blue blocks are called “processors.” They do something with those numbers inside the program.</li></ul><p>Now we can add a yellow block. This is called an output. Outputs use numbers to make something happen in real life or in simulations.</p><p>Click the “demo output” to add a tile to your workspace. Use the dropdown menu to change it into a gripper.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
