      {
        "id": "fFbg3GAPJKvshVU_",
        "title": "Text 6",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Right now the gripper is 0% closed. We want to figure out how it works: can we make it fully closed or partially closed?</p><p></p><p>Connect the gripper to your program (or to a different program you design!) and try to figure out:</p><ol><li><strong>How do you make the gripper close 100%?</strong></li><li><strong>Can you make the gripper partially closed? (e.g., 25% closed, 50% closed, 90% closed)</strong></li><li><strong>If no, why not? If yes, how? Is there a percent closed that it </strong><strong><em>can&#x27;t</em></strong><strong> do?</strong></li></ol><p></p><p>You might ask &quot;But what do I connect it to?&quot; or &quot;What is my program supposed to look like?&quot;</p><p>As you saw earlier, there isn&#x27;t just one way to make things work in programming!</p><p>Throughout these lessons, you will be developing strategies for designing and making new programs!</p><p>Try to think: what is a way to connect this to figure out the problem? If you&#x27;re not sure, try one way you can think of to connect it, even if you&#x27;re not sure it&#x27;s the best way. If it doesn&#x27;t help you, you can think about a better way later!</p><p></p><p>Drag the table below to your workspace and fill as many rows as you need to help you keep track of what you have tried and to notice any patterns.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "lPa1Ieo7nV-yYQk4",
        "content": {
          "type": "Table",
          "columnWidths": {
            "C6gQsA4izXFWHC8o": 238,
            "9Rr45TV5X9UpGHSI": 234
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "Vc46EZlPhDDKA0dB",
        "title": "Documenting the Gripper",
        "content": {
          "type": "Question",
          "version": 1,
          "locked": false,
          "questionId": "m7GTcP",
          "tiles": [
            {
              "title": "Question Prompt",
              "fixedPosition": true,
              "content": {
                "type": "Text",
                "format": "html",
                "text": [
                  "<p>1. An important part of writing programs is documenting what you figure out so that others can use the new ideas, and so that you remember what you did next time you want to use the program. Explain how the gripper works to someone who has never used it before.</p><p></p><p>2. We are also trying to develop some strategies for figuring out how to make programs work. Maybe you used a good strategy, and maybe you think you can improve your strategy.</p><p>In the second space, explain to someone who is getting started with Dataflow what you suggest they do to figure out what a new block does.</p>"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "title": "Text 9",
              "content": {
                "type": "Text",
                "format": "html",
                "text": [
                  "<p><strong>How the gripper works:</strong> </p>"
