      {
        "id": "Vgc6qoEDt_gV8hAb",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<h2>Class Gallery</h2><p>So far, you worked together with your group, but in CLUE you can also see what other groups did. If you click the purple &quot;Class Gallery&quot; tab, you can see the work that other students in your class have worked on.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "muWZ2shXQUjLh0Hz",
        "title": "Noticing Differences",
        "content": {
          "type": "Question",
          "version": 1,
          "locked": false,
          "questionId": "bIswUY",
          "tiles": [
            {
              "title": "Question Prompt",
              "fixedPosition": true,
              "content": {
                "type": "Text",
                "format": "html",
                "text": [
                  "<li>Look through the other programs your classmates made.</li><li>Find one group that connected the gripper to the program differently than your group OR one group who suggested a different strategy for figuring out what blocks do.</li>"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "title": "Text 7",
              "content": {
                "type": "Text",
                "format": "html",
                "text": [
                  "<p><strong>Which group:</strong></p><p><strong>What was different about how they connected their gripper, or about their strategy?</strong></p><p><strong>Do you think your way or their way is better for figuring out what blocks do, or were they both equally good? Why?</strong></p>"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
